    "Id": "chassisdef_hatamoto-chi_HTM-35X",
    "Name": "Hatamoto-Chi",
    "Details": "A Jihad-era Experimental prototype variant that was made in an attempt to design a mass-produced Amphibious Assault 'Mech. Based on the HTM-27T, the original model has its Endo Steel internal structure swapped for a composite internal structure. Its short-range missile launchers are replaced by a pair of 15-Tubed Long-Range Torpedo Launchers and a pair of 4-Tubed Short-Range Torpedo Launchers. The LRTs have two tons of ammo, while SRTs have only one. Its PPCs are replaced by Snub-Nose PPCs in each of its fully actuated arms. The 35X also has been given secondary surface weapons, in the form of five medium lasers. To handle its heat issues, the 'Mech been given 10 Double heat sinks. This prototype has been reconverted for land combat again, replacing the torpedoes with missiles.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Easy to Maintain</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.19</color></b>\n\n<br><br><color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limit: Left Lower</color>",
